song_name: Eat That Up Its Good For You

version_description: Chords are right according to the live on Jimmy Kimmel performance (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kLw3m31OJBs), which is the same as the album version.
Odd timing and changes throughout the song, so listen to the album version and you'll be able to pick it up pretty quick.

I've seen Many versions of this song's chords but I don't think any of them are actually correct. I'm pretty much sure these are the actual chords for the song basing on the acoustic version played only by the vocalist of the band and his guitar

Well for a lot of beginner guitarists, some people may not have capo's. So I took the chords that were relative to a capo on the 5th fret and I made them regular chords you could play in Standard tuning and it sounds the same.
